TextJPN: 夜になり、俺たちが夕食を食べかけていたところに、電話がかかってきた。
TextENG: After nightfall, right as we were about to eat dinner, a phone call came in.

TextJPN: 準備をひと通り終えたばかりのおふくろが、玄関口へと駆けだしてゆく。
TextENG: Mom, who had just finished making preparations, rushed over toward the front door.
``Huh?@k@vS07/01/330100213. I wonder who it is.@k@vS07/01/330100214. Could it be about Rena?!``

TextJPN: まさにその予感通り、電話はレナのお父さんからだった。
TextENG: Just as I predicted, it was a call from Rena's father.

TextJPN: 「も、もしもし！@k@vS07/01/330100218.　どうも、こんばんは！」
TextENG: ``H-Hello?@k@vS07/01/330100218. Yes, good evening!``

TextJPN: 「夜分遅くにすみませんね。@k@vS07/00/VT2A_renaF1002.そちらにウチの礼奈がおうかがいしていませんか。@k@vS07/00/VT2A_renaF1003.夕方頃に急に家を飛び出したっきりまだ帰ってこないんです」
TextENG: ``I apologize for calling this late.@k@vS07/00/VT2A_renaF1002. Is Reina there?@k@vS07/00/VT2A_renaF1003. She ran out of the house earlier this evening and hasn't come back.``

TextJPN: 「急に家を飛び出した？！@k@vS07/01/330100220.　あの、どんな様子でしたか」
TextENG: ``She ran out of the house?@k@vS07/01/330100220. Umm, how was she?``

TextJPN: 「礼奈が悪ふざけをする時のような、猪突猛進な感じでね。@k@vS07/00/VT2A_renaF1005.てっきり、誰かお友達の家かと思ったんだが……」
TextENG: ``Well, she was in a headlong kind of run, like when she's playing a prank on someone.@k@vS07/00/VT2A_renaF1005. I'd thought she was going to one of her friend's houses...``

TextJPN: 「……間違いない。@k@vS07/01/330100222.誰かが白の勾玉を拾ったんだッ！！」
TextENG: ``...That settles it.@k@vS07/01/330100222. Somebody picked up the white magatama!!``

TextJPN: 「遅れてごめんなさいですわー！！」
TextENG: ``I'm very sorry for being late!!``

TextJPN: 「……どんな状況なのですか」
TextENG: ``...What's the situation?``

TextJPN: 「うん、今からレナの部屋に入れてもらうところ。@k@vS07/03/330300106.学校での傾向から見るに、きっと室内に何らかの痕跡が残されてるよ」
TextENG: ``We just got permission to go into Rena's room.@k@vS07/03/330300106. Judging by how she was acting at school, she must have left some clues in there.``

TextJPN: 「だなぁ。@k@vS07/01/330100224.そう言えば俺、レナの部屋に入るのって初めてだよ。@k@vS07/01/330100225.…何だか緊張するなぁ！」
TextENG: ``Yeah.@k@vS07/01/330100224. Come to think of it, I've never been in Rena's room before.@k@vS07/01/330100225. ...Makes me kind of nervous!``

TextJPN: 「「うっわぁあぁぁ……」」
「何となく想像はついちゃいたが…、すっげえ部屋だなぁ。@k@vS07/01/330100227_1.散らかっているのか小物だらけで満載なのか区別がつかないぞ！」
TextENG: ``I had a feeling, but... This room is really something.@k@vS07/01/330100227_1. I can't tell whether it's a collection of trinkets or just a mess of junk!``

TextJPN: 「……それでいて本人にはどこに何があるのか、ちゃんとわかっていたりするんですけどね」
TextENG: ``...And yet she knows exactly where to find each and every one of her treasures.``

TextJPN: 「相変わらずすごいなぁ。@k@vS07/03/330300109.よくもこれだけ色々溜め込むもんだよねぇ…。@k@vS07/03/330300110.レナの前世は犬だね！@k@vS07/03/330300111.　きっと靴とかを大量に集めてたに違いないよ」
TextENG: ``It's just as terrific as she is.@k@vS07/03/330300109. How did she fit all these things in here?@k@vS07/03/330300110. She must have been a dog in her past life!@k@vS07/03/330300111. I bet she liked collecting a lot of shoes and stuff.``

TextJPN: 「俺さぁ、女の子の部屋ってもっと片付いてて、女の子らしいきゃぴきゃぴした部屋なんだって思ってたんだが、@k@vS07/01/330100229.あれって男の幻想なのかなぁ？@k@vS07/01/330100230.　レナの部屋もこんなだし、魅音の部屋だって漫画だらけでこんな感じだったぜ？」
TextENG: ``I always thought girl's rooms would be like... more tidy, more cute and bright and girly...@k@vS07/01/330100229. Maybe that's just a misconception that guys have.@k@vS07/01/330100230. I mean, Rena's room is like this, and Mion's room has comics laying around everywhere.``

TextJPN: 「あははははは、おじさんは女の子じゃないからねぇ～！」
TextENG: ``Ahahahaha, well, this old man isn't a little girl, after all~``

TextJPN: 「…あれぇ？@k@vS07/06/330600073.　多分それはお姉の漫画部屋の方ですよ？@k@vS07/06/330600074.　圭ちゃんはお姉の本当の部屋に入ったことはないんですか？@k@vS07/06/330600075.　母屋じゃなくて離れにある…、むがッ！！」
TextENG: ``...Huh?@k@vS07/06/330600073. I think that was just Sis's manga room.@k@vS07/06/330600074. Kei-chan, have you ever been in Sis's actual room?@k@vS07/06/330600075. Not in the main building, the one farther away— mmff!!``
``Sh-Shion!!@k@vS07/03/330300114. Shhhh!! Shhhh!!!``

TextJPN: 「あー、見てくださいな！@k@vS07/04/330400173.　ほら、レナさんの机の上にこんなにも本が！！」
TextENG: ``Ah, would you look at this!!@k@vS07/04/330400173. Look at all the books over here!!``

TextJPN: 沙都子が指差す先には、レナの学習机。そこには読み散らして積み上げた本の山があった。
TextENG: Satoko pointed over at Rena's desk. A big pile of books, some open, sat on top of it.

TextJPN: 「今度は何の本だ？！@k@vS07/01/330100232.　ん～？@k@vS07/01/330100233.　なんかのハードカバー本か？@k@vS07/01/330100234.　図書館で借りてきたのかな。@k@vS07/01/330100235.何々、『現代メイド理論』『メイドの道は一日にして成らず』『美しきご奉仕とは』。@k@vS07/01/330100236.…何だ、みんなメイドの本じゃないか」
TextENG: ``What kind of books is it this time?!@k@vS07/01/330100232. Hmm~?@k@vS07/01/330100233. Hardcover books of some sort?@k@vS07/01/330100234. Did she borrow these from the library?@k@vS07/01/330100235. Let's see... 'Modern Maid Theory,' 'The Way of the Maid is not Walked in a Day,' 'What is Beautiful Service.'@k@vS07/01/330100236. ...What the? They're all books about maids?``
...Hmm?

TextJPN: 「「な、なんだとおぉおおぉおぉ？！」」
TextENG: ````Wh-what the heeeeck?!````
